{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 While the  metadata entry for LyX looks similar to the entry for LaTeX, it really only has one function for LyX. Since natbib is used by default in LyX, either citations need to be compatible with \'91Author-Year\'92 (see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#citations"}}{\fldrslt {\i Citations}}}) or you can specify the value  for . This changes the citation style in natbib to numeric to avoid errors. This is the same as is described in the MultiMarkdown User\'27s Guide{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chtfn {\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Fletcher T. Penny
