{\pard \s3 \f1\fs28\ql\sb240\sa180\b {\*\bkmkstart lyxheadings}{\*\bkmkend lyxheadings}Lyx Headings\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 When MultiMarkdown is used to create LaTeX output, users have a metadata entry called  which controls which MultiMarkdown heading level corresponds to a LayTeX heading level. The  defines how far down the LaTeX hierarchy the first MultiMarkdown level corresponds.
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Because the LyX support is intended to encompass a broader set of LyX classes than just Memoir and Beamer, a metadata entry called  is provided. The value is a comma separated list of LyX environments in order from the highest level to the lowest level. Up to seven levels can be provided. If fewer than seven items are provided, they replace the equivalent number with the rest remaining the defaults.
