{\pard \s3 \f1\fs28\ql\sb240\sa180\b {\*\bkmkstart numberheadings}{\*\bkmkend numberheadings}Number Headings\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 LyX users can choose to have headings automatically numbered, or they can remain unnumbered. In LyX this is done by selecting an \'93environment\'94 with or without a trailing asterisk. Environments without an asterisk are numbered, those with an asterisk are not numbered.
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Thus choosing the  environment results in a numbered header and choosing the  environment results in an unnumbered heading.
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 In MultiMarkdown this is controlled with the  metadata entry. If a value of  is provided, headings are not numbered. Any other value (or not providing this metadata entry) results in numbering the headers.
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 If numbering is requested, links will reference the numbering associated with the target of the reference. If numbering is turned off, appropriate links to the text of the target will be used.
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Please note that if you turn off numbering, and use LyX to create a PDF file, it will not have table of contents bookmarks, making your PDF more difficult to navigate.
\par}

