{\pard \s2 \f1\fs28\ql\sb240\sa180\i\b {\*\bkmkstart citations}{\*\bkmkend citations}Citations\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Because LyX uses natbib, in order to be compatible citations must be in a particular format known as the \'91Author-Year\'92 format. This format requires the Author\'27s last name followed by the year in parenthesis.
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 The example in the MultiMarkdown User\'27s guide:
\par}

{\pard \s7 \qj\sa180\f2\fs20\li360\ri360 This is a statement that could be attributed to its source [p. 23][#Doe:2006]\
\
And following is the description of the reference to be used in the bibliography.\
\
[#Doe:2006]: John Doe. *Some Big Fancy Book*. Vanity Press, 2006.\

\par}


{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Would be re-written as:
\par}

{\pard \s7 \qj\sa180\f2\fs20\li360\ri360 This is a statement that could be attributed to its source [p. 23][#Doe (2006)]\
\
And following is the description of the reference to be used in the bibliography.\
\
[#Doe (2006)]: John Doe. *Some Big Fancy Book*. Vanity Press, 2006.\

\par}


{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Resulting in:
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 This is a statement that could be attributed to its source {\super\chftn}{\footnote\ftnalt\pard\plain\chtfn {\pard \s7 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24\li360\ri360 John Doe. {\i Some Big Fancy Book}. Vanity Press, 2006.
\par}
}
\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 Alternatively you could use the  metadata element described in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#latexinput"}}{\fldrslt {\i LaTeX Input}}} to change the citation style to numbers.
\par}

{\pard \s2 \f1\fs28\ql\sb240\sa180\i\b {\*\bkmkstart tables}{\*\bkmkend tables}Tables\par}

{\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 The standard LaTeX footnote command  doesn\'27t work in normal tables{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chtfn {\pard \s0 \qj\sa180\f0\fs24 For LyX see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wiki.lyx.org/LyX/Tables#footintab"}}{\fldrslt http://wiki.lyx.org/LyX/Tables#footintab}}\line For LaTeX see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.tex.ac.uk/cgi-bin/texfaq2html?label=footintab"}}{\fldrslt http://www.tex.ac.uk/cgi-bin/texfaq2html?label=footintab}}
\par}
}. Therefore, when MultiMarkdown converts a document to LyX format, all tables that are created are LyX \'93long tables.\'94 Not only do long tables support proper footnotes, they also can span pages if required. LyX provides a number of options for controlling long tables and you can take advantages of these once in the LyX environment. MultiMarkdown sets the expected default options.
